        <td style="padding:0px 10px 20px 10px;line-height:24px;text-align:inherit;"
            height="100%"
            valign="top"
            bgcolor="">
            <div>Last newsletter, we talked about <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/worklab/work-trend-index/great-expectations-making-hybrid-work-work">Microsoft's report</a> on the benefits and struggles of hybrid work.</div>

<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div><a href="https://www.bbc.com/worklife/article/20220120-why-hybrid-work-is-emotionally-exhausting">This BBC article</a>, analyzing a TinyPulse survey on hybrid work, rings some alarm bells about exhaustion and digital presenteeism in hybrid setups.</div>

<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div>In fact, the number of hybrid employees signaling exhaustion (72%) was double that of fully-remote workers, and also higher than fully office-based workers. Oof.</div>

<div>&nbsp;</div>

<div>If that's you, what are some ways to make a more&nbsp;a sustainable day? We've curated some tips to help you out with:</div>

<ul>
	<li><a href="https://arc.dev/developer-blog/wfh-remote-work-distractions/?utm_source=sendgrid&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=arc-newsletter&amp;utm_content=20220419">Managing distractions</a>&nbsp;(so you get more done faster)</li>
	<li><a href="https://arc.dev/developer-blog/how-to-stay-motivated-at-work/?utm_source=sendgrid&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=arc-newsletter&amp;utm_content=20220419">Staying motivated</a> (because some days are harder than others)</li>
	<li><a href="https://arc.dev/developer-blog/time-management-skills/?utm_source=sendgrid&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=arc-newsletter&amp;utm_content=20220419">Managing your time</a> (and not doing unnecessary overtime)</li>
</ul>
        </td>
      </tr>
